<TITLE> Now Khaleda accused of code breach </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 11 (bdnews24.com)  After the prime minister, the opposition leader has now been charged with breaching electoral codes. The allegation was brought by Ishaq Mia, chief election agent for the Awami League-backed mayoral candidate ABM Mohiuddin Chowdhury. Chowdhury is seeking an unprecedented fourth term as mayor in the June 17 polls under the banner of Citizen Committee. Ishaq on Friday sent a letter to the district returning officer, secretary general of the committee Emdadul Islam confirmed bdnews24.com. The complaint states that BNP chairperson Khaleda Zia held a teleconference in the wee hours of Thursday in Khulshi with the opposition party's top leaders, who were in a meeting with M Manzur Alam, the BNP-backed candidate. Reports on the meeting were published in different newspapers on Thursday and Friday. She breached the code by holding the teleconference, the complainant added. Earlier on Thursday, a senior BNP leader alleged the same code breach against prime minister Sheikh Hasina, saying that she had asked two influential Hindu community leaders of Chittagong to influence Hindus in favour of Mohiuddin. The Chittagong district election office acknowledged to have received the complaint. b
